title: For Sale:  S.I.A De Lisle Silent Carbine 45ACP
postcontent:
S.I.A. DeLisle Silent Carbine in .45ACP sold new to me by S.I.A. in 2013. Excellent condition, only about 50 rounds through it. On Form 4 in Wisconsin.  Includes original plastic case and cleaning gear. 
S.I.A., or Special Interest Arms, is owned and operated by Richard Brengman, Gardnerville, NV. He manufactures these De Lisle carbines similar to but not exactly like the original WWII British commando sentry take-out weapons.  Like the originals, they are built using a MK III Lee-Enfield action, butt stock and modified bolt.  The barrel is a 10" Thompson SMG barrel and 16" integrated suppressor.  Unlike the original, the baffles are stainless steel and the magazine adapter allows for use of unmodified 1911 .45ACP magazines. These guns are made in very limited numbers, and are very quiet. Examples can be viewed on Youtube.

title: For Sale:  Glock 29 Competition Parts Kit
postcontent:
Up for sale are the parts I purchased for my G29.  The SS Compensated Barrel and Tungsten guide rod/spring combination reduces muzzle flip and greatly reduces felt recoil.  I fired exactly 3 mags, (45 rounds) with the barrel and guide rod so it is like new.  Also included is a Ghost 3.5 lb Trigger Control Connector, this connector reduces trigger pull by 25% and also shortens the trigger pull stroke by 60%.  Allows shooting faster and better.  In addition there is a Lone Wolf Extended Slide Lock and Extended Slide Stop Release

KKM Precision Stainless Steel Barrel for Glock 29 Match - 10mm Drop in -  with 10mm Compensator Part # G29G1C.  The compensator reduces muzzle flip and also reduces felt recoil.  All KKM barrels are made using U.S. manufactured 416R Stainless steel bar stock which is then heat treated and vacuum tempered to 42RC. All Barrels are CNC machined to obtain superior dimensional tolerances. Using our unique Button Rifling process, all KKM barrels offer superior accuracy over stock barrels. Our Glock barrels come with fully supported match chambers for shooting factory or reloaded ammunition as well as lead or jacketed bullets.  The compensator has a few places where the finish is scratched and will be priced accordingly.

Super Heavy Duty Tungsten Guide Rod and 21 lb Spring – Fits Glock 29, 29SF, 30, 30SF, and 36.  This spring and guide rod reduces felt recoil in half.  You can shoot the hottest loads comfortably with this installed.  Just drops in, no gunsmith needed.  The 21 lb spring enables reliable feeding of the hottest 10mm loads available.

Ghost Connector shortens the total length of trigger pull and reset enabling you to shoot faster and better. Faster because the total distance the trigger has to move to fire your pistol is reduced up to 60%. Better because once the pistol fires the trigger movement is stopped. Stopping the trigger after the pistol fires is critical to bullet placement. No trigger movement + no pistol movement = no sight movement on the target-this eliminates accuracy robbing over-travel. The bullet goes where you aimed it! Shorter & faster reset-because the Connector eliminates all over-travel of the trigger so that the trigger moves less in both directions.

I paid:  
KKM SS Barrel with Compensator  -  $275.00 + $10.00 shipping = $285.00
Tungsten Guide Rod & 21 lb Spring - $69.95 + $7.50 S&H = $77.45

If you're browsing this T-series you probably know what you're looking for in this 9mm.

But I have to tell you that the FRONT SIGHT on this Hi Power flew off, and I can't bring myself to ruin the bluing by resoldering it back on. Nor do I want to undo the "all original" factor with new sights (which requires heavy metal modification on the slide).

I still HAVE the sight, as seen pictured, but it is not seated permanently. 

Slight hair scratch/blemish here and there on the surface, with minor pitting on the passenger side of slide. So basically what you have here is an 80% Blued T-series waiting to be modded.

Grips are original with red backing and probably in 70% condition. The compression on the photos of ARMSLIST makes images look crummy, but I assure you this firearm is a beauty, despite it's age.

If you're looking for a project or don't mind the blue scarring from resoldering, then this piece is for you.

Sturm, Ruger & Company, Inc. (NYSE: RGR) is excited to introduce the Ruger® SR1911® Lightweight Commander-Style pistol; an aluminum frame version of the popular SR1911 Commander-Style pistol. This new model features a black anodized aluminum frame with a satin stainless finish on the slide, resulting in an attractive two-tone appearance in a gun that weighs 7oz. less than the all stainless steel version. It comes factory equipped with an integrated, polished titanium feed ramp and features thin, hardwood grip panels for concealed carry, as well as front strap serrations for improved grip.Ruger engineers took a hard look at how they could utilize new materials to improve the performance of the aluminum-framed 1911. Most aluminum frame pistols tend to show excessive wear on the feed ramp, particularly when shooting modern hollow-point ammunition. This can result in unreliable feeding and may be expensive to correct. The new SR1911 Lightweight Commander-Style pistol comes factory equipped with an integrated polished titanium feed ramp for a lifetime of reliable performance.Since entering the 1911 market in 2011, Ruger has quickly become known for producing some of the best quality 1911's available today. These American-made, CNC machined, series-70 design 1911's come standard with many features typically found only in custom manufactured pistols. All SR1911's feature Novak LoMount Carry 3-dot sights, a lowered and flared ejection port, and a titanium firing pin. In addition, each Ruger SR1911 features a precision barrel and bushing which are machined to match from the same piece of bar stock. The frames have an integral plunger tube, beaver-tail grip safety, oversized magazine release, extended thumb safety and a skeletonized hammer and trigger for fast, accurate shooting. All of this, without the price tag of a custom gun.With the addition of this aluminum frame, commander-style model to the SR1911 line, customers now have a lightweight carry option with the rugged reliability of a Ruger. The SR1911 Lightweight Commander-Style pistol features a 4.25" barrel and weighs 29.3 oz. with an empty magazine. It ships with two 7-round magazines, a bushing wrench, cable locking device, and a soft case.
